 prohibit even its indirect detection, our results\nare discussed within the context of an evolutionary sequence of activity\ntriggered by close galaxy interactions and merging. We argue that the non-HBLR\nSy2 galaxies may represent different stages of this sequence, possibly the\nbeginning and the end of the nuclear activity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Aug 2014 20:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 10 Nov 2014 10:05:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-11"}
